{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"pillared-doddering-fawn","description":"The `test` GitHub Actions workflow's `lint + type-check` job fails on EVERY push to\n`main` (the post-merge branch CI + the Gerrit `Verified` mirror both run\n`pre-commit run --all-files`). Root cause: commit `703661409`\n(`compliable-stretchy-bee`, ticket e72b) added the `no-commit-to-branch` pre-commit\nhook with `args: [--branch, main, --branch, master]`. That hook is a LOCAL,\ncommit-time guardrail (\"don't commit directly to main\"), but CI legitimately checks\nout and runs `pre-commit run --all-files` while HEAD is on `main`, so the hook fires\nand fails the whole job. The real enforcement of \"land through Gerrit\" is\nserver-side (GitHub ruleset + the two Gerrit votes); the hook was never meant to gate\nCI.\n\nEvidence: run 29470200567 (branch `main`) fails at\n`pre-commit ... don't commit to branch...Failed` → `Process completed with exit\ncode 1`. The only recent GREEN run (29464899221) was on a FEATURE branch\n(`test/fd84-guardfire`), where the hook passes because HEAD is not main/master.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n- [ ] Check out `main` (as CI does on a push-to-main event).\n- [ ] Run `pre-commit run --all-files --show-diff-on-failure` (the exact CI step).\n- [ ] Observe `no-commit-to-branch` reports `Failed` and the command exits 1.\n\n## Expected vs Actual\n- Expected: on a legitimate CI checkout of `main`, `pre-commit run --all-files`\n  runs the code-hygiene + lint/typecheck hooks and passes; the local-only\n  `no-commit-to-branch` guardrail does not gate CI.\n- Actual: `no-commit-to-branch` fires because HEAD is `main`, failing the\n  `lint + type-check` job (and it would fail the Gerrit `Verified` mirror on any\n  checkout that lands HEAD on a real `main`/`master` branch).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The CI `pre-commit run --all-files` step in `.github/workflows/test.yml`\n      skips the `no-commit-to-branch` hook (via `SKIP=no-commit-to-branch`),\n      verifiable by inspecting the step's `env:` block in the file.\n- [ ] The same skip is applied to the mirrored `pre-commit` step in\n      `.github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml` (Verified gate), for consistency and\n      to prevent latent breakage if that checkout ever lands HEAD on `main`.\n- [ ] The `no-commit-to-branch` hook remains present and unchanged in\n      `.pre-commit-config.yaml` (the local commit-time guardrail is preserved, not\n      removed), verifiable by diff.\n- [ ] Locally reproduce the skip working: `SKIP=no-commit-to-branch pre-commit run\n      no-commit-to-branch --all-files` reports the hook as `Skipped`, confirming the\n      env var is honored by the pinned pre-commit.\n- [ ] `make lint` and `make typecheck` remain green (no Python changed; YAML-only).","id":"ae0e-1cfa-cc92-4b1e","parent_id":"","priority":1,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"CI lint job fails on every main push: no-commit-to-branch hook fires in pre-commit run --all-files"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784227193874560001,"uuid":"6c919da8-099f-43f5-b537-2d8c36f31160"}